title: Essay on the "Tuesday Club" of Peterson, Iowa
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Essay on the Tuesday Club of Peterson, Iowa. Heywood describes memories of the club, of which she was chairman, while her mother, Charlotte Kirchner Butler, was the organization's first president. Essay states that it was written about 50 years after the Club's founding, which, according to the document, was either in 1908 or 1909.
